1.desc: A microwave oven Sirius bought herself. Despite seeing heavy use, it somehow looks as pristine as the day it was purchased.
1.name: Microwave Oven

2.desc: Sirius uses this to make coffee every morning.The machine still has traces of her fingerprints on it.
2.name: Coffee Machine

3.desc: The pair of shoes that Sirius wears all the time. They are loved and cared for, and thus the leather retains its soft luster.
3.name: Mary Janes

4.desc: The subject is an orange tabby wearing a blue necktie. Behind the apparent sophistication lies a silly but cute appeal. It's safe to say the tenant likes this particular kind of cuteness.
4.name: Wall-Mounted Photograph

5.desc: A very practical machine for the novice at-home cook. Drop in some bread slices, push down, and soon you'll have hot, crispy toast. You can of course adjust how toasty you want it.
5.name: Toaster

6.desc: Also known as a "rubbish bin" in some parts of the world. You look and you look, but you can't find anything unusual about this wholly unremarkable waste receptacle.
6.name: Trash Can

7.desc: This frame doesn't have a proper photo in it yet. The placeholder image is just there to look more appealing than a plain beige background.
7.name: Blue Sky Picture Frame

8.desc: The pattern on its wings reminds you of a wave washing up on a shore, and of Sirius sprinting across the sea, her hair fluttering in the wind. You should invite Sirius to go on a walk on the beach the next time you're free.
8.name: Preserved Butterfly

9.desc: A floor lamp standing just by the couch. Sirius graciously thought ahead and picked a bulb that wouldn't strain your eyes. You could see yourself working from here every now and then.
9.name: Floor Lamp

10.desc: Two sandwiches and a croissant. Baked by Sirius, from the looks of it. Although they look and smell perfectly fine, you probably shouldn't taste them until Sirius urges you to.
10.name: Bread Plate

11.desc: A book lying on the table by the bed. Sirius has been reading this one quite a lot lately. After flipping through a few pages, you figure out that it's a story about a forbidden love between a maid and her master.
11.name: Recreational Reading

12.desc: They're filled not with wine, but water. A perfect illustration of the kind of service Sirius provides. Although, drinking water from a wine glass with your pinky extended is a chore. You should tell her to get some regular glasses someday.
12.name: Wine Glasses

13.desc: A replica of the hero's sword from the smash hit port virtual reality RPG. The stand says, "For Kitchen Adventures." It's no wonder why the one in Sirius' room feels so much heavier.
13.name: Legendary Sword Replica

14.desc: One of the fruits of Sirius' practicing of flower arrangement. While it isn't very varied in color, the flowers are distributed well. These would look better in a more open place.
14.name: Flower Arrangement 1

15.desc: A pile of books lying by the bedside. Surprisingly, they're not all about cooking – they cover subjects like military tactics and how to provide optimal service. Sirius' personal notes are layered between the books. Judging by their contents, she's diligently studying to become an even better maid.
15.name: Bedside Books

16.desc: Sirius must have been in a rush to see you, because she forgot to put the cap back on her lipstick. Be kind and do it for her!
16.name: Dresser

17.desc: An expensive piece of jewelry. Sirius hasn't worn it even once, preferring to keep it nice and safe behind the glass.
17.name: Jewelry Case

18.desc: A pair of pretty yellow roses. They bring a sunny mood to whatever table they find themselves atop. You start to wonder what flower is Sirius' favorite.
18.name: Flower Arrangement 2

19.desc: A mystery book yet to be even opened. One can assume this genre isn't Sirius' cup of tea for the time being.
19.name: Mystery Novel

20.desc: It has writing on its stomach that reads, "EXPERTLY CRAFTED BY AKASHI." Sirius is a regular patron of hers.
20.name: Stuffed Shiba Inu

21.desc: The float ring Sirius used when you went to the beach with her. It's placed in a very eye-catching location inside her home. Being a maid, she's hesitant to ask her master to go swimming with her for fear of making a faux pas. So instead, you should be the one to ask her.
21.name: A Summer Memory

22.desc: A storage box for regular workbooks. Sirius says the notepads outline her maidly work schedules. You see half-faded writing on the label on the cover. "The Ways I Want to Be --------" it says – half of the title has been almost completely erased.
22.name: Box of Books

23.desc: A watering can keeps the potted plants and flowers around the room happy. This is not a watering can. It's very blatantly a teapot. You wonder what bizarre thinking led Sirius to start using this in place of a proper watering can.
23.name: Watering Pot

24.desc: A nightlight with an endearing design.Sirius got it so she wouldn't trip and fall when she gets up at night.Its warm light reminds you of the warmth of her smile.
24.name: Nightlight

25.desc: The pair of sunglasses Sirius brought with her to the beach.She leaves them where they're always in reach.
25.name: Sunglasses

26.desc: Sirius uses this body lotion after her baths.Sometimes, you can smell its faint aroma even from the door to her quarters.
26.name: Body Lotion

27.desc: This diffuser exudes a mild floral scent. Sirius chose it with great care.The aroma supposedly relieves stress and helps the mind relax.
27.name: Aroma Diffuser

28.desc: This white towel was haphazardly left here. It's still slightly moist to the touch.Maybe Sirius just got done in the bathroom? Who knows.
28.name: White Towel

29.desc: A book Sirius left by her bedside.What is this book doing here?Also, they made TWO volumes of this?
29.name: How to Win Your Commander's Heart - Volume 2

30.desc: Half full, or half empty? Either way, it's sitting on the table and has faint lip markings along its rim.
30.name: Half-Drunk Milk

31.desc: This sandcastle shines golden under the sun. Its builder put clear effort into everything down to the smallest details.You can readily picture just how much work was put into it.Here's hoping that the waves won't wash it away.
31.name: Splendid Sandcastle

32.desc: A shovel and a bucket lying in the sand. Looks like someone was using them until just a minute ago.You think to yourself that maybe you should have a sandcastle-building contest next time you visit the beach with someone.
32.name: Beach Tools

33.desc: A wooden guitar, forgotten and left behind by its own. Brine lingers inside its cavity, and it smells like the sea. Its notes sound almost like the lapping of waves on a beach.
33.name: Seabreeze Guitar

34.desc: A partially drunk beverage. It's still cold, with drops of condensation gently running down its sides. Whoever this belonged to earlier, the beached has claimed it now.
34.name: Half-Consumed Drink

35.desc: These surfboards have been casually left here. Their many scratches whisper stories about past encounters with fierce waves. Maybe you should go surfing the next time you visit the beach with someone.
35.name: Surfboards

36.desc: A cute little cooler. Someone must have packed for some sort of party, because it's stuffed full of drinks and snacks. You can't help but wonder where its owner has gone.
36.name: Cooler

37.desc: Two inner tubes, one in blue and one in yellow, silently resting on the beach. While they look pretty old, they are still able to do their job perfectly well.
37.name: Inner Tubes

38.desc: A trash can with a humble design. Remember: don't litter on the beach! Keeping it clean is just as important as keeping the oceans clean.
38.name: Trash Can

39.desc: A lantern with a simple design. When it gets dark at the beach, this can be a real lifesaver. It's all but begging to be brought along on a fantastical nightly stroll along the sea.
39.name: Lantern

51.desc:
The delectable dango rest quietly on a ceramic plate,
perfectly complementing the tablecloth's design.
Enjoy them with her later.
51.name: Hanami Dango Plate

52.name: Tri-Color Mochi

53.desc:
A book on traditional Sakuran tea ceremonies,
its corners slightly weathered.
Noshiro appears to revisit this book often,
leaving many neat notes on the last pages.
53.name: Opened Book

54.desc:
Neatly folded bedding.
The precise corners are a testament to its owner's diligence.
54.name: Bedding

55.desc:
The uniform hanging on the wall is the same as the one she is wearing.
Looks like this is the outfit she likes the most.
55.name: Uniform

56.desc:
A beautifully arranged assortment of Sakuran sweets, each handmade by Noshiro.
Though they may almost be too pretty to eat,
be sure to savor them later – lest her hard work will go to waste!
56.name: Sakuran Sweets

57.desc:
A wind chime hangs by the window,
producing a clear melody as the breeze passes through.
According to Noshiro, it's one of the best ways to beat the summer heat.
57.name: Wind Chime

58.desc:
This wind chime produces a deeper tone than the glass one.
Noshiro has purposefully hung it up elsewhereso the different notes interweave, creating a unique mood.
58.name: Wind Chime 2

59.desc:
A paper bag bearing a coffee shop logo.
Noshiro treats it with great care,
more than you'd expect for a regular paper bag.
59.name: Shopping Bag

60.desc:
The gold-thread embroidery on this kimono's sleeves speaks of its elegance.
It's Noshiro's favorite.
She always conducts herself carefully when she wears it outside.
60.name: Sakuran Kimono

61.desc:
Yellow roses carefully preserved inside a bell jar.
The petals retain their vivid color even to this day.
61.name: Preserved Flowers

62.desc:
A small pine tree bonsai.
The branches have been trimmed in a plain yet tasteful way.
Noshiro tends to it daily, preserving its natural beauty in perfect form.
62.name: Pine Bonsai

63.desc:
A Sakuran ornament that typically goes in the garden but, in this case, has been placed in a corner of the room.
When water flows in, it produces a clear and pleasant sound.
63.name: Water Ornament

64.desc:
This folded umbrella rests against the wall.
Noshiro often carries it with her when she goes outside.
When it's raining, obviously.
64.name: Sakuran Umbrella

65.desc:
A round cushion in a bright color.
While it looks firm at a glance, it's surprisingly comfy to sit on.
Maybe you should put one in your office too?
65.name: Round Cushion

66.desc:
A tray lined with hand-formed sushi and other delicacies.
Every item is meticulously placed,
and even the decorative elements are well-thought-out.
Surprisingly, sushi rolls are even included.
Turns out Noshiro isn't a stickler for tradition.
66.name: Sushi Platter

67.desc:
A cherry blossom branch left on the table.
The pink petals almost glow on the branch, lending a touch of spring mood.
67.name: Cherry Blossom Branch

68.desc:
A stack of books piled atop one another.
The subjects covered range from tea ceremonies to flower arrangement and traditional etiquette.
Based on where the bookmark is, Noshiro is studying a new flower arrangement technique.
68.name: Stack of Books

70.desc:
An unremarkable kettle.
Noshiro often uses it when making tea.
Despite its signs of heavy use, it's still in good condition thanks to diligent care.
70.name: Kettle

71.desc:
A lantern made of stone, inspired by traditional Sakuran garden lanterns.
It lends an air of tranquility to wherever it's placed.
71.name: Stone Lantern

72.desc:
These scrolls rest quietly in the corner of the study,
their knots perfectly tied.
Though not unfurled, they still convey Noshiro's meticulous care.
72.name: Tied Hanging Scrolls

74.desc:
A square, wooden lantern that's been placed in a corner.
A soft light glows through the translucent paper.
Noshiro picked this furnishing after careful deliberation.
74.name: Wooden Lantern

75.desc:
An austere Sakuran-style floor lamp. It glows with a soft light.
Beneath its shade hangs a delicate wind chime ornament.
It creates a quiet, serene space where you can spend a peaceful time with Noshiro.
75.name: Floor Lamp

76.desc:
This white humidifier operates silently most of the time,
only sometimes making a faint hum.
Noshiro placed it in a corner where it can slowly release moist air.
She says it's good for her skin.
76.name: Humidifier

77.desc:
The oil inside the bottle emits a delicate fragrance.
According to Noshiro, it's extracted from camellias.
It's one of her favorite skincare products.
77.name: Skincare Oil

78.desc:
A bottle of perfume with a simple design.
Light softly reflects off its glass surface.
Upon closer inspection, you notice that this is the very bottle you gifted her.
78.name: Perfume Bottle

79.desc:
A diffuser with a delicate fragrance.
Its subtle aroma fills the room.
It's the scent that always lingers around Noshiro.
79.name: Reed Diffuser
